FAHDU – How a User Becomes a Creator
Apply for Creator (Get Verified Process)
If a regular user wants to become a creator, they must use the Get Verified option from Settings.
 Step 1: Start Verification
Go to Settings
Click on Get Verified
Fill in required details
 Step 2: Basic Information
Creator must provide:
Profile Image
Cover Image
Full Name
Display Name
Date of Birth
Select Niche (Category)
After filling details → Click Next
 Step 3: Instagram Verification
Enter Instagram account name
Using the Instagram handle, send a verification code to FAHDU’s official Instagram ID
Click Submit
This step confirms social identity and authenticity.
 Step 4: Admin Review
Verification request is sent to Admin
Review time: Up to 24 hours
Admin checks if the user meets creator criteria
 Result Notification
User receives an email:
 Verification Passed
 Verification Failed (with reason mentioned)
 After Approval – Creator Activation Process
Once verification is approved:
User must relogin to the FAHDU app
Creator Terms & Conditions screen appears
User must:
Toggle agreement button
Click “Agree & Continue”
After this step → User account becomes a Creator account.
 First-Time Creator Onboarding Process
When creator logs in for the first time, an onboarding process starts.
Creator Onboarding Setup
Creator must configure:
Chat Fee (per message)
Audio Call Fee
Video Call Fee
Live Stream Fee
Subscription Fees
Follower/Subscriber pricing (if applicable)
Creator must fill all required details.
After completing onboarding:
Creator account becomes fully active
Creator profile goes live
Users can now follow, chat, subscribe, and book calls

how creator use add post feature
The Add Post feature allows creators to upload images or videos and share them with followers or subscribers.
 Accessing Add Post
Creator clicks on the 3rd icon in the bottom navigation bar
Clicks on the 1st icon (Create Post)
This opens the post creation screen.
 Upload Content
Creator can:
Upload Image
Upload Video
Content is selected from device gallery.
Apply Audience Filter
Creator can choose who can view the post:
Followers only
Subscribers only
Public (if available)
This allows creators to control content access.
Add Text (Optional)
Creator can:
Add caption/text
Or post without text
Text is optional.
Schedule Post (Optional)
Creator can:
Select date & time
Schedule the post for future publishing
If not scheduled → Post will publish immediately.
Publish Post
After completing setup:
Click Post Button
Image/Video gets uploaded
Post is published on creator’s account

How Creator Uses Chat Feature
 Basic Chat Functionality
Creator can chat with users (followers/subscribers).
Chat is free when creator replies to users.
If a creator wants to chat with another creator:
Chat is paid
Coins are deducted as per chat fee rules.
 Messaging Capabilities
In chat, creators can:
Send text messages
Send images
Send videos
Send documents
These can be:
 Free
 Paid (PPV – Pay Per View)
If content is paid:
User must unlock the file
Coins are deducted from user wallet
User can view that specific content
Content can be sent:
With text
Without text
Followers & Subscribers View
On the chat screen, creators can see:
List of Followers
List of Subscribers
This helps creators identify:
Who is following
Who is subscribed
Who is eligible for special pricing
Label Feature
Creators can assign labels to users for better management.
Example purposes:
High spender
Regular supporter
New follower
VIP user
Labels help creators:
Organize users
Filter users later
Send targeted messages

How Creator Uses Mass Message Feature
Mass Message allows creators to send the same message/content to multiple users at once.
Step 1: Open Mass Message
Go to Chat
Click on Mass Message icon
Step 2: Apply Filters
Creator can select audience based on:
Required (Selected Users)
All Users
Followers
Subscribers
Labels
Online Users
Offline Users
Random Users (system selects random users)
 Step 3: Add Content
Creator selects:
Image or Video
Add Text (optional)
 Step 4: Choose Pricing
Creator decides:
Send as Free Content
 OR
Send as Paid Content (PPV)
 Step 5: Send
Same file/message is sent to multiple selected users
If paid:
Users must unlock individually
Coins deducted per user

How Creator Starts a Live Stream
Step 1: Open Live Stream
From Navbar, click on the Third Icon
Click on the Live Stream icon
A popup appears asking to Accept Live Stream Terms
Click Accept
After accepting → Live Stream settings page opens.
 Live Stream Settings Page
On the Live Stream settings page, creator can see:
 Fee Structure
Live stream fee for Followers
Live stream fee for Subscribers
These fees are based on the creator’s configured pricing.
Add Live Goals
Creator can add goals to motivate users during live stream.
 Goal Setup
Click Add Goal
Enter:
Goal Title (Example: “New Mobile”)
Goal Amount (Example: 10,000 coins)
 Goal Rules
Creator can add maximum 3 goals at a time
If 1 goal out of 3 is completed:
Creator can add 1 new goal
This keeps total active goals limited to 3.
 Select Audience
Before starting live stream, creator must choose who can join:
Option 1: Followers & Subscribers
Option 2: Subscribers Only
Creator selects one option based on preference.
Start Live Stream
After setting:
Fees
Goals
Audience type
Creator clicks Start Live Stream
Live stream begins.
During Live Stream
Users join based on eligibility
Users pay coins based on their role (Follower / Subscriber)
Users can:
Send tips
Help complete goals
If any goal reaches its target:
Goal is marked completed
Creator can add a new goal
End Live Stream
When creator finishes:
Click End Live Stream
Summary screen appears showing:
Total coins earned from live entry
Total tips received

How Creator Earns from Referral Feature
Creators can earn by inviting other creators to join FAHDU.
 Referral Process
Creator shares their profile referral link
Another creator joins FAHDU using that referral link
The invited user completes verification and becomes a creator
The referred creator starts earning on the platform
Referral Earning Logic
If the referred creator earns ₹30,000 per month
The original (referring) creator earns 5% commission
5% is calculated from the referred creator’s monthly earnings
Commission is credited on each payout cycle of the referred creator
Important Rules
Referral reward applies only when the invited user becomes a verified creator
Earnings are percentage-based
Commission is recurring (on each payout)

How Creator Earns from Wishlist Feature
Wishlist allows creators to set financial goals that followers can support.
Step 1: Create Wishlist
Go to Profile Page
Open the Third Tab – Wishlist
Click Create New Wishlist
 Step 2: Add Wishlist Details
Creator must add:
Wishlist Title
Description
Image
Click Next
 Step 3: Set Amount
Enter target amount (in coins)
Click Upload
Wishlist becomes visible to users.
 Wishlist Completion
Users contribute coins toward wishlist
When target amount is reached → Wishlist is marked completed
 Payout Process
After wishlist is completed:
Creator clicks Request Payout
Amount is processed
Creator receives payout directly into bank account
Important Notes
Wishlist is goal-based earning
Payout is available only after goal completion
Instant payout after approval

How Creator Earns from Subscription Feature
Creators can earn recurring income through subscriptions.
 Subscription Setup (During Onboarding)
While setting up creator account, creator configures:
Monthly Subscription
3-Month Subscription
6-Month Subscription
12-Month Subscription
Creator can:
Set price for each duration
Add discount on longer plans
Example:
1 Month – Standard Price
6 Months – Discounted
12 Months – Higher Discount

How Earnings Work
User subscribes to creator
User pays subscription fee
Creator earns subscription amount
Subscription remains active for selected duration
Benefits of Subscription
Recurring income
Exclusive content access
Special pricing for subscribers
Stable monthly earning source

How Creator Earns from Call Feature (Audio/Video Call)
Call Request Process
When a user wants to connect via Audio or Video call:
User sends a call request from chat
User selects call duration (e.g., 10 min, 30 min, etc.)
Required coins are put on hold from user wallet
Creator Call Request View
On the creator side:
In the chat section, there is a Call Requests area
Creator can see:
List of users who requested calls
Requested call duration
Call type (Audio / Video)
 Scheduling the Call
Creator can:
Accept the call request
Schedule the call time
Connect with the user at the scheduled time
 Call Attempt Rule
Creator has 3 attempts to connect the call
If call connects successfully → Conversation starts
If call fails after 3 attempts → Call is cancelled
If cancelled:
Coins are refunded to user
 Creator Earnings from Call
If call connects successfully:
Call timer starts
Creator and user talk
After call ends → Coins are finalized
Creator earns based on:
Their fee setup
User type:
Follower rate
Subscriber rate
Call duration
Longer call duration = Higher earning.
 Earnings Logic
Creator earning depends on:
Per minute call rate
Role-based pricing (Follower / Subscriber)
Total connected call time

how creator use setting option
The Settings section allows creators to manage their profile, subscriptions, revenue, security, and account preferences.
Edit Profile
Using Edit Profile, creator can update:
Full Name
Display Name
Bio
Description Title
Description
After editing → Click Save
View Profile
Creator can click View Profile to see their public profile.
Inside profile:
 Contact Info Section
Creator can add custom text for:
Video Call
Audio Call
Live Stream
Chat
 Fee Display
Profile also shows:
Subscriber fee
Follower fee
 For:
Chat
Audio Call
Video Call
Live Stream
Subscribed
Shows list of creators this creator has subscribed to.
Status shown:
Active
Inactive
Subscribers
Shows list of users/creators who subscribed to this creator.
Displays:
Active subscribers
Inactive subscribers
 Followers
Shows full followers list.
Following
Shows list of accounts the creator is following.
Change Password
Creator can:
Enter current password
Enter new password
Confirm new password
Save changes
Referral
Shows:
Total referral earnings
Referral creator list
Commission received from each referral
Manage Revenue
This section includes:
1. Transactions
Shows all transactions:
Credit (CR)
Debit (DR)
Includes earnings from:
Chat
Tip
Audio/Video Call
Live Stream
Subscription
Referral
2. Dashboard
Displays:
Total earnings
Payout-to-payout earnings
Feature-wise earning breakdown
Payout Process
Creator adds payout amount
Submit payout request
Amount is transferred to bank account within 24 hours
3.Fee Setup
Creator sets pricing for:
Chat
Audio Call
Video Call
Live Stream
Pricing rule:
Subscriber price = Full price
Follower price = 50% of subscriber price
Creator can also upload display image for subscription/following section.
4. Subscription Fee
Creator can change subscription pricing anytime for:
1Month
3 Months
6 Months
12 Months
Discounts can also be updated.
Wallet
Creator can:
Check wallet balance
Purchase coin packs
Blocked Users
Shows:
Blocked users list
Blocked creators list
Creator can unblock from this list.
Scheduled Content
If creator has scheduled posts, they appear here.
Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
Creator can:
Enable/Disable 2FA using toggle
OTP is sent to registered email
After OTP verification → 2FA is activated
Linked Accounts
Creator can connect account with:
Apple ID
Google Account
 Terms & Conditions
View FAHDU Terms & Conditions.
Privacy Policy
View FAHDU Privacy Policy.
Refund Policy
View FAHDU Refund Policy.
 About
Shows:
App version
Basic app information
Help Center
